column2: Algae near surface in some places
Some weeds above surface- 3" rain yesterday- blue heron visitor for past 3 years.  Water level: up some
Used to be lots of little Bluegills- saw 1st this year last week
Cloudy and high winds day before
Flock of cranes flying s- also geese
Saw 5 loons three weeks ago by pier.
The weeds have started to surface already.
Ample rain- lake in good shape.
Lake level lowest ever.  Recent rain has helped situation.
Thank god for the fall rain.
Water high for time of year.
Lake high for this time of year.
Slight chop on water.  Sunny- warm.
Hazy with light breeze. Warm.  Ruddy duck and mallard sitting on limb together.
2 families of geese with about 10 total goslings- heavy pollen- bluegills starting to spawn
saw the loon- heavy algae bloom
water level way down- beautiful day
saw bald eagle and 11 geese- slight chop
water level is way down- very windy
water level still down- algae floating on surface (small amount)
water level way down- beautiful day- light breeze
Saw family of geese and full grown family of mallards.
Bald eagle was fishing.  Saw lots of little bluegills.

column1: very windy- probably cost us a few feet

column2: lots of pollen on water loon was out
late in day with slight chop
algae bloom ended - lake may have turned over day before
A Loon- Wood Duck- Mallard- and Common Merganzer was on the lake.
Lots of stuff floating on top of water.
Algae Bloom going on. A bald Eagle was flying around. The water was cloudy with some chop.
Over cast with light chop. A heavy algae bloom.
Lake is very clear. and calm
Slight chop. Baby ducks. Mallards- wood ducks and Mergansers
Bald Eagle was fishing. Heavy algae bloom
Nice day . Sunny with a little chop.
A slight chop. Turtles in the tree.
Warm spring. Big storm last night. Water cloudy
It was windy and the lake looked like it was full of algea. Scuba dove and found the same.
Windy and sunny. Still lots of algae.
Calm with pollen on the lake
Saw a loon . Lake had a light chop.
Haze on the water due to an algae bloom. Cotton Wood heavy
Choppy and overcast. Had a hard time holding the boat.

Found a 5 quart pail full of Hi-bred milfoil around the lake. Including 3 plants on the south east end of the lake. The Loon has been around all summer. Hooded Mergansers- Mallards and Wood Ducks had little ones- as well as 2 families of geese
